# Immutable Sandbox Laws

## 1. The Zero-Waste Mandate
Explicitly forbidden to run `npm install` for state management, routing, or heavy UI utility libraries. You must mandate the use of native React hooks and the existing lightweight IPC router.

## 2. The WebWorker Physics & ELK Math Engine
All WebWorkers (specifically the `elkjs` layout engine for the TDA Canvas) MUST be instantiated using Vite's blob-inlining strategy (`import Worker from './worker?worker&inline'`) to bypass `vscode-webview://` protocol restrictions. Never import heavy computation libraries directly into the React component thread.

## 3. Visual Strictness
Forbidden to use raw hex codes or standard CSS frameworks. Enforce the exclusive use of native VS Code CSS variables (e.g., `var(--vscode-editor-background)`) to guarantee host-theme compliance.

## 4. IPC Boundary Enforcement
The `src/webview` (React/Chromium) cannot access the file system/`vscode` API natively. The `src/extension` (Node.js Host) cannot access the DOM.
